Aneka Tambang, Astra International: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-07-25T01:50:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-25/aneka-tambang-astra-international-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  gained 1 percent to 4,106.82.  Energy companies: Crude oil futures declined as much as 1.1
percent to $98.74 a barrel in after-hours trading in New York as
of 8:45 a.m. Jakarta time, set for the first drop in five days.  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC IJ),  Indonesia ’s
biggest listed oil company, jumped 4.3 percent to 2,425 rupiah
and PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG IJ), the second largest, surged
9.8 percent to 225 rupiah.  PT Aneka Tambang (ANTM IJ): Gold rose to a record on demand
for an investment haven as failure to raise the U.S. federal
debt limit intensified concern of a default. Gold for August
delivery climbed as much as 1.4 percent to $1,624.30 an ounce in
 New York . Aneka, an Indonesian gold and nickel producer, climbed
1.2 percent to 2,050 rupiah.  PT Astra International (ASII IJ): The company’s unit, PT
Toyota-Astra Motor, is confident that it can maintain its share
of the Indonesian car market at 36 percent in the second half,
Marketing Director Joko Trisanyoto said. The company’s sales
rose to 152,283 units in the first half from 140,396 units in
the same period a year earlier, it said. Astra, Indonesia’s
largest automotive retailer, rose 2.3 percent to 72,900 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  